      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REPELLENT (1) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 3.5 lengths at Sandown in a handy 29.65 beating Pumping Magic. Draws the cherry and goes well over this trip. Can make it back-to-back wins. PAW HARRIS (8) turned in a better effort at Horsham last start, finishing third behind Cheeky Mila (23.54) in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Can feature again. ILLUMINATOR (7) was safely held in tougher company last start after missing the jump at this track, but prior to that won comfortably by 6 lengths at Sandown (29.43) beating Nosey Bluey in a Grade 5 on April 16. Likely to play a prominent role. HARTLAND WILLOW (2) has hardly put a foot wrong of late and will be competitive again.",
